What is Industrial grade 3D printing?

Industrial grade 3D printers are built for productivity, with rugged components that deliver reliable printing day and night, year after year. Tested and tuned for plug-and-print ease, long term accuracy and the highest standards of safety. Desktop 3D printers simply can’t deliver the high level of accuracy, durability and performance required by professionals.
“For us, choosing the Stratasys F123 series was simple. We needed repeatable accuracy 1st time every time – a machine that keeps on working around the clock with minimal fuss straight out of the crate. Our F370 is the core of our business. Coming from using high-grade toolroom CNC equipment I am used to quality, and this machine has performed above my expectations.”
Andrew Kelly CEO of Design 3D Print Shed

Textured and Flexible Build Tray

Ensures strong part adhesion during printing and easy part removal when part is complete.

Key Features of the Stratasys F123 Series

  • Closed-Loop Servo Motors (Accuracy & Reliability)
    Provide precise head positioning, speed and motion control for superior part quality
  • Durable Steel Frame and Linear Profile Rails (Durability & Accuracy)
    Handle a higher load capacity, providing the rigidity needed for speed and accuracy.
  • Patented Airflow (Accuracy & Reliability)
    Maintains consistent temperature across the build area for perfect extrusion and adhesion of materials, resulting in better Z-strength.
  • Double Wall Oven with High Quality Insulation (Accuracy & Safety)
    Keeps the inside of the oven hot – for accurate parts – and outside the oven cool to touch for safety.
  • Kevlar Belts (Durability & Reliability)
    Provide the right tension without wear and stretching over time allowing printing up-time instead of calibration and replacement.
  • Textured and Flexible Build Tray (Reliability & Accuracy)
    Ensures strong part adhesion during printing and easy part removal when part is complete
  • Insulation Accordion (Accuracy)
    Maintains correct temperature while build heads move in the X-Y plane.
  • Safety Features (Safety)
    Built-in sensors monitor heat, power and print success. Door and hood remain locked.
  • Meets Global Compliance Standards (Safety)
    Limits emissions, interference with other powered equipment and meets CE & UL certifications.

Stratasys F123 Series Features

Stratasys F123 Series 3D printers look great on the outside but the real beauty lies within. High-quality, precision tuned components along with over 50 sensors and over 58 patents work behind the scenes to ensure years of reliable, accurate and safe performance. Explore the highlighted areas for more details on key F120 features.

    Reliability

    Stratasys F123 series printers, including the F120, are made with quality components and are backed by over 250,000 hours of testing to deliver 100% reliability with long term accuracy and performance. Whether you need to print a single complex part or many parts with repeatable accuracy, the F123 Series gives you hassle free results. Just hit print and relax. Every system is powered up and tested for print results before it ships. Performance you can rely on.

      Accuracy

      Stratasys F123 series printers are built to make sure what you designed is the print you get. Stratasys produces each F120 to exacting specifications, and it shows in the dimensional accuracy of your print results. From superior patented temperature control and insulation to Kevlar belts that never wear out, everything about the F123 printers is designed for precision 3D printing every time. Don’t believe it, let us prove it to you.

        Durability

        The F123 Series printers are built for long term performance. Quality components like the steel box frame, linear profile rails and servo motors ensure quality prints day after day, year after year. The F120 is built with quality components meant for frequent printing. When other printers fail, the F123 printers will still be producing like the workhorse printers they are. Quality components are the key to years of continuous productivity, don’t settle for less.

          Safety

          Safety and F123 Series printers go hand in hand. Stratasys takes safety seriously, and you can see it in the F123 features like a lock that prevents the door from opening until the oven has cooled to a safe temperature. The F123 printers have been through rigorous compliance testing to make sure it’s safe to use in a variety of working environments. Run your printer knowing your staff or students are safe from moving parts and heat.
